        <h3><a href="../comment/18166#comment-18166" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Windows 8 bug....and workaround...</a></h3>
    
    <div class="content">
      <div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>There is currently a Windows 8 bug with Gimp Book, that I believe is in pyGtk, an upstream library I use for Gimp Book. I've reported it to pyGtk, but don't know if there is a fix yet ( <a href="https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=720366">bug report</a> ). I haven't tested on earlier versions of Windows, but it's likely happening on all Windows versions.</p>
<p>When you try to choose a folder, such as choosing a destination for a new book, the plug-in will crash. I've found two workarounds, but neither is great.</p>
<p>This only seems to happen in Gimp 2.8 and 2.10 on Windows, so using earlier versions it should work correctly.</p>
<p>Or, you can avoid clikcking anything in the popup menu. Just use the mouse to open it, but then use the arrow keys and return, to select from it. For some reason this does not crash the plug-in.</p>
<p>If I don't hear anything back from the pyGtk folks, I'll probably try to write a workaround for it in Gimp Book.</p>
</div></div></div>          </div>
  </div>

